combine half of the sake mixture with the chicken pieces and toss to coat. Cover dish and place in refrigerator for about 30 minutes.", "In a medium frying pan, combine remaining sake mixture, chillies, vinegar and sugar. Mix together and add spring onion, garlic, water chestnuts and peanuts. Heat sauce slowly over medium heat until aromatic.", "Meanwhile, remove chicken from marinade and sauté in a large frying pan until juices run clear. When sauce is aromatic, add sautéed chicken and let simmer together until sauce thickens."]'::jsonb, 'http://allrecipes.co.uk/recipe/1773/kung-pao-chicken.aspx', 'https://www.themealdb.com/images/media/meals/1525872624.jpg', TRUE, 2, TRUE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('nutty-chicken-curry', 'Nutty Chicken Curry', 4, 0, 0, '{"calories": 606, "protein": 16.8, "carbs": 70.7, "fat": 31.0, "saturated_fat": 10.7, "polyunsaturated_fat": 0.0, "monounsaturated_fat": 3.7, "sodium": 382.2, "potassium": 221.3, "fiber": 7.0, "sugar": 39.2, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 20.0, "calcium": 277.7, "iron": 1.7}'::jsonb, ARRAY['chicken', 'indian', 'themealdb', 'nutrition-generated', 'soup'], '[{"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "serving", "item": "Red Chilli", "notes": null, "category": "other"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "serving", "item": "0.5 Ginger", "notes": null, "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "serving", "item": "Garlic", "notes": null, "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "serving", "item": "Coriander", "notes": null, "category": "spices"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "Sunflower Oil", "notes": null, "category": "pantry"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "serving", "item": "Breasts", "notes": null, "category": "other"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "serving", "item": "Peanut Butter", "notes": null, "category": "dairy"}, {"quantity": 150.0, "unit": "ml", "item": "Chicken Stock", "notes": null, "category": "meat"}, {"quantity": 200.0, "unit": "g", "item": "Greek Yogurt", "notes": null, "category": "dairy"}]'::jsonb, '["Finely slice a quarter of the chilli, then put the rest in a food processor with the ginger, garlic, coriander stalks and one-third of the leaves. Whizz to a rough paste with a splash of water if needed.", "Heat the oil in a frying pan, then quickly brown the chicken chunks for 1 min. Stir in the paste for another min, then add the peanut butter, stock and yogurt. When the sauce is gently bubbling, cook for 10 mins until the chicken is just cooked through and sauce thickened. Stir in most of the remaining coriander, then scatter the rest on top with the chilli, if using. Eat with rice or mashed sweet potato."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/11753/nutty-chicken-curry', 'https://www.themealdb.com/images/media/meals/yxsurp1511304301.jpg', TRUE, 4, TRUE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
