e", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "roasted sesame seeds", "notes": "1 tbsp. roasted Sesame seeds", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "tomatoes", "notes": "½ cup of chopped tomatoes", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "pinch", "item": "turmeric", "notes": "Pinch of turmeric", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.5, "unit": "cups", "item": "button mushrooms", "notes": "1 ½ cups sliced white button mushrooms", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "", "item": "to", "notes": "½ to ¾ tsp garam masala", "category": "ethnic foods"}]'::jsonb, '["Recipe at my blog"]'::jsonb, 'https://spoonacular.com/-1464612078182', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/773671-312x231.jpg', TRUE, 4, TRUE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('chinese-veg-fried-rice', 'Chinese Veg Fried rice', 4, 0, 0, '{"calories": 430, "protein": 7.36, "carbs": 81.04, "fat": 7.71, "saturated_fat": 1.17, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 3907.11, "potassium": null, "fiber": 2.37, "sugar": 5.12, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 3.98, "calcium": 36.01, "iron": 1.07}'::jsonb, ARRAY['chinese', 'asian', 'side dish', 'antipasti', 'starter', 'snack', 'appetizer', 'antipasto', 'hor d''oeuvre', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan', 'spoonacular', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "cups", "item": "basmati rice", "notes": "2 cups Basmati rice or any long grain", "category": "pasta and rice"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "garlic if you prefer. at home garlic is used to a minimum and barely a hint", "notes": "1/2 tbsp minced garlic or more if you prefer. At home garlic is used to a minimum and barely a hint.", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "small", "item": "chillis", "notes": "2 small green chillis chopped fine", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "olive oil", "notes": "2 tbsp sesame oil or olive oil.", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "tsp", "item": "pepper flakes", "notes": "1/4 tsp red pepper flakes", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tsp", "item": "pepper powder", "notes": "1 tsp white pepper powder,", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "salt", "notes": "2 tablespoons salt", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "soy sauce to give a stronger colour but we prefer the rice to remain little and dont really care", "notes": "1 tbsp soy sauce or more to give a stronger colour but we prefer the rice to remain little white and dont really care for the soy taste.", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "spring onions", "notes": "1 tbsp spring onions finely diced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "greens of spring onions", "notes": "2 tbsp greens of Spring onions.", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "chilli sauce if you prefer a spicier one", "notes": "2 tbsp chilli sauce or more if you prefer a spicier one.", "category": "ethnic foods"}]'::jsonb, '["Cook the Basmati rice with 2 1/2 cups of water and add a tsp of oil too before pressure cooking. After one whistle , take it off and keep the rice cool by fluffing it out with a fork.Chop all vegetables uniformly like long strips. I used red and yellow bell peppers and cut them into strips.I also used fresh corn kernels,French beans,Spring onions.Take a large wok which works best for a good stir fry.", "Heat the wok well , and add some oil and start by seasoning with chopped green chillies, minced garlic. Stir fry the spring onions,", "Add the bell peppers and stir briskly on a high flame as we want the vegetables to cook lightly and retain the crunch.", "Add the pre cooked corn kernels and remaining vegetables.", "Add the cold fluffed out Basmati rice and mix well with the vegetables, keep stirring and add the soy sauce, green chilli sauce, red pepper flakes, white pepper,salt and add little sesame oil .When the fried rice is still hot lastly add the greens of the spring onions as it will retain the nice crunch and the colour after the rice is done.", "Serve hot ."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/TTSVHLSH/chinese-veg-fried-rice', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/638729-312x231.jpg', TRUE, 3, TRUE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('asian-marinated-eggplant', 'Asian Marinated Eggplant', 6, 0, 0, '{"calories": 24, "protein": 1.54, "carbs": 3.34, "fat": 0.79, "saturated_fat": 0.12, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 543.32, "potassium": null, "fiber": 1.38, "sugar": 1.57, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 6.28, "calcium": 11.39, "iron": 0.58}'::jsonb, ARRAY['asian', 'side dish', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'fodmap friendly', 'vegan', 'spoonacular', 'grilling', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "cilantro", "notes": "2 tablespoons Loosely packed cilantro (coriander or chinese", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 8.0, "unit": "oz", "item": "mediums sized eggplants", "notes": "4 mediums Sized (2 oz. each) Chinese eggplants *", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.375, "unit": "ounce", "item": "ginger", "notes": "3/8 ounce Peeled fresh ginger (1 by ¼ piece cut", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 6.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "parsley) leaves", "notes": "Parsley) leaves", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tablespoon", "item": "rice wine vinegar", "notes": "1 tablespoon Rice wine vinegar", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "sesame oil", "notes": "1 teaspoon Toasted sesame oil", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "tamari", "notes": "1/4 cup Tamari", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "inch", "item": "inch crosswise into ¼", "notes": "inch Crosswise into ¼ slices", "category": "?"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "inch", "item": "crosswise into ¼", "notes": "inch Crosswise into ¼ slices", "category": "?"}]'::jsonb, '["* (Here they call them Japanese - the small skinny light purple or lavender ones)", "Combine all ingredients EXCEPT EGGPLANT in a blender or processor. Process until smooth. Prick th eggplants several times with a fork and pull off the leaves.", "Cut in half lengthwise. On the open side of each half make three deep diagonal slashes in each direction.", "Place eggplants skin side down in a 13x9x2 oval dish.Spoon 1 1/2 teaspoons of the marinade over each eggplant half. Rub into flesh so that it runs into the cuts. Turn eggplants skin side up.", "Pour remaining marinade into the dish.", "Let stand 45 minutes.Turn eggplants skin side down. Cover tightly with microwave plastic wrap.Cook at high power for 10 minutes. Prick plastic to release steam.", "Remove, uncover, spoon sauce over eggplants.", "Serve as side dish. Recommended with grilled fish steak or chicken breast (of course I''d baste that with a soy based marinade).I may try this over a wok steamer rather than in the microwave.WHICH REMINDS ME: Stephen, I love a dish which I have seen referred to as Yu Shaing Eggplant. Based on a Yu Shaing sauce. Which is, to some extent, translated as fish sauce (I know the yu or ju is fish) not made from it but to go with it, I gather. It is certainly not nuoc mam but I don''t know if it contains it. It is rather hot and by flavor I would guess it comes from the northern provinces - perhaps NE end of China. I have also had it with fresh pork strings. Glorious. Do you have any idea what it is or a recipe??? I have been unable to find it anywhere in my Chinese library. The restaurant where I eat it is not one to give recipes or ingredients to non-Chinese (if they''d give it to the Chinese. The place is popular with the newer Chinese community here. (The old timers are all Cantonese and so well integrated that they probably consider red beans and rice their d"]'::jsonb, 'http://www.foodista.com/recipe/W4KWFG6Z/asian-marinated-eggplant', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/632849-312x231.jpg', TRUE, 3, TRUE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('japanese-pickles', 'Japanese Pickles', 6, 0, 0, '{"calories": 41, "protein": 1.49, "carbs": 8.67, "fat": 0.35, "saturated_fat": 0.04, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 104.31, "potassium": null, "fiber": 1.79, "sugar": 5.63, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 7.87, "calcium": 34.78, "iron": 0.5}'::jsonb, ARRAY['japanese', 'asian', 'side dish', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan', 'spoonacular', 'grilling', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "chili peppers", "notes": "3 Fresh red chili peppers seeded", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "", "item": "japanese cucumbers", "notes": "4 Japanese cucumbers thinly sliced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "cilantro", "notes": "2 tablespoons Fresh cilantro", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "onion", "notes": "1 Red onion, thinly sliced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "teaspoons", "item": "rice syrup", "notes": "2 teaspoons Rice syrup", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 1.5, "unit": "teaspoons", "item": "rice vinegar", "notes": "1 1/2 teaspoons rice vinegar", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "salt", "notes": "1/4 teaspoon Salt", "category": "spices and seasonings"}]'::jsonb, '["Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.", "Serve as a compliment to grilled or spicy foods, or with chicken or fish.Store in a Japanese pickle press."]'::jsonb, 'http://www.foodista.com/recipe/HBL5F77J/japanese-pickles', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/648487-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 5, TRUE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('mango-fried-rice', 'Mango Fried Rice', 2, 0, 0, '{"calories": 486, "protein": 15.96, "carbs": 95.36, "fat": 4.03, "saturated_fat": 1.03, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 404.1, "potassium": null, "fiber": 4.94, "sugar": 4.39, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 17.67, "calcium": 56.72, "iron": 2.17}'::jsonb, ARRAY['chinese', 'asian', 'side dish', 'lunch', 'main course', 'main dish', 'dinner', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'spoonacular', 'soup'], '[{"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "cups", "item": "chicken stock", "notes": "2 cups of chicken stock", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "seasoning cubes", "notes": "Seasoning cubes", "category": "meat"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "slices", "item": "mango", "notes": "3 slices of mango cubed", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "cup", "item": "rice", "notes": "1 cup of rice", "category": "pasta and rice"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "cup", "item": "vegetables", "notes": "1 cup of chopped vegetables", "category": "frozen"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "scotch bonnet pepper", "notes": "1 scotch bonnet pepper", "category": "produce"}]'::jsonb, '["Wash your rice and bring to boil on medium heat with very little water as you are still going to cook it in chicken stock.Once the rice is slightly soft and the initial water has dried up, reduce the heat and pour in the chicken stock and cook till the chicken stock is all absorbed and has dried up. The chicken stock if freshly made will have some oil from the chicken so your rice does not need oil.Increase the heat and stir in the chopped vegetables and pepper.", "Add your seasoning cube.Finally stir in your cubed mango and serve warm with any protein of your choice. I’d say chicken but it’s up to you."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.afrolems.com/2015/05/02/mango-fried-rice/', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/716311-312x231.jpg', TRUE, 3, TRUE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('gluten-free-dairy-free-sugar-free-chinese-chicken-salad', 'Gluten Free Dairy Free Sugar Free Chinese Chicken Salad', 6, 0, 0, '{"calories": 363, "protein": 30.96, "carbs": 28.7, "fat": 15.42, "saturated_fat": 2.62, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 317.98, "potassium": null, "fiber": 6.91, "sugar": 16.18, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 95.11, "calcium": 186.18, "iron": 3.13}'::jsonb, ARRAY['chinese', 'asian', 'side dish', 'lunch', 'main course', 'salad', 'main dish', 'dinner', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'spoonacular'], '[{"quantity": 5.0, "unit": "ml", "item": "apple cider vinegar", "notes": "1 tsp. (5ml) of organic apple cider vinegar", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "pepper", "notes": "1 teaspoon crushed black pepper", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.5, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "sesame seeds", "notes": "1 1/2 tablespoons black sesame seeds", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "carrots", "notes": "3 carrots", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "C", "item": "extra virgin olive oil", "notes": "1/4 C extra virgin olive oil + 7-8 Tbsp for frying", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "", "item": "cabbage", "notes": "1/2 green cabbage", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "kosher salt", "notes": "1/2 teaspoon kosher salt", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 6.0, "unit": "", "item": "satsuma mandarins", "notes": "6-8 fresh satsuma mandarins", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "", "item": "cabbage", "notes": "1/2 red cabbage", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "chicken breasts roasted", "notes": "3 chicken breasts (bone in, preferably organic) roasted and shredded", "category": "meat"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "bunches", "item": "romaine lettuce hearts", "notes": "2 bunches romaine lettuce hearts", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 6.0, "unit": "", "item": "scallions", "notes": "6 scallions", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "sesame oil", "notes": "3 tablespoons sesame oil", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "juice of 1 mandarin (cut crosswise then tablespoon into jar over a strainer)", "notes": "juice of 1 mandarin (cut crosswise then tablespoon into jar over a strainer)", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "sesame seeds", "notes": "3 tablespoons white sesame seeds", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.5, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "xylitol", "notes": "1 1/2 tablespoons xylitol (I use Epic Dental brand)", "category": "health foods"}]'::jsonb, '["For the salad:Finely slice the red, and green cabbage.", "Remove ends and finely slice romaine lettuce.Trim ends of scallions (white and green side) and finely slice.Peel and grate carrots, or put into a mini food processor to finely chop.Peel clementines then remove pith from slices.", "Add all the ingredients into a glass jar and shake until well blended, or whisk all the ingredients in a mixing bowl.", "Pour dressing over salad, toss to combine well.If making ahead, dress the salad just before serving."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/ZSNGMXBF/gluten-free-dairy-free-sugar-free-chinese-chicken-salad', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/644826-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 1, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('winter-kimchi', 'Winter Kimchi', 1, 0, 0, '{"calories": 365, "protein": 23.01, "carbs": 73.22, "fat": 3.36, "saturated_fat": 0.67, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 1437536.75, "potassium": null, "fiber": 16.19, "sugar": 31.78, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 281.48, "calcium": 1700.49, "iron": 17.53}'::jsonb, ARRAY['korean', 'asian', 'side dish', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'pescatarian', 'spoonacular', 'dessert'], '[{"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "small", "item": "napa cabbage", "notes": "1 small napa cabbage, (abt ½ kg) quartered lengthways with stems attached and washed", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "liters", "item": "brine solution", "notes": "Brine solution (3- 4 liters water+ 1 ½ cups coarse salt)", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "chilly paste / korean gochujang paste", "notes": "3 tablespoons chilly paste (reduce for less spicy)/ korean gochujang paste", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "", "item": "bowl rice", "notes": "1/4 bowl cooked rice", "category": "pasta and rice"}, {"quantity": 150.0, "unit": "grams", "item": "radish", "notes": "150 grams radish, julienned", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 40.0, "unit": "grams", "item": "spring onions", "notes": "40 grams spring onions, cut into abt 2\" lengths", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 15.0, "unit": "grams", "item": "chilly flakes", "notes": "15 grams chilly flakes", "category": "cereal"}, {"quantity": 10.0, "unit": "grams", "item": "sugar", "notes": "10 grams sugar", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "garlic bulb", "notes": "1 whole garlic bulb, skinned", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "fermented baby shrimps/ cincalok", "notes": "2 tablespoons fermented baby shrimps/ cincalok (you can even use brined fish/anchovies)", "category": "seafood"}, {"quantity": 0.125, "unit": "cup", "item": "fish sauce", "notes": "1/8 cup fish sauce", "category": "ethnic foods"}]'::jsonb, '["Soak the quartered cabbage in the brine solution for 4 hours, weighing the cabbage down with a heavy plate.", "Remove and drain.", "Place garlic cloves, rice, fermented shrimp, fish sauce, sugar, chilly paste and chilly flakes in a food processor and zap to a smooth paste. Stir in spring onions.", "Stuff the cabbage with the paste, making sure to stuff in between the individual leaves and coating every inch of it.", "Place kimchi into an airtight container and leave at room temperature for a day before leaving it to ferment further in the fridge for at least another week before consuming. I left mine for about 3 weeks."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/DPZ3FLTW/winter-kimchi', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/665379-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 5, TRUE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('asian-coleslaw-with-baked-salmon', 'Asian Coleslaw with Baked Salmon', 4, 0, 0, '{"calories": 687, "protein": 46.22, "carbs": 58.61, "fat": 32.86, "saturated_fat": 4.84, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 129.24, "potassium": null, "fiber": 15.71, "sugar": 8.54, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 38.37, "calcium": 92.96, "iron": 4.68}'::jsonb, ARRAY['asian', 'side dish', 'gluten free', 'pescatarian', 'spoonacular', 'salad', 'baking'], '[{"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "an avocado", "notes": "An avocado, sliced and served on the side.", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 200.0, "unit": "gr", "item": "oz. beansprouts", "notes": "200gr / 7 oz. beansprouts", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 200.0, "unit": "gr", "item": "oz. carrot", "notes": "200gr / 7 oz. grated carrot", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "", "item": "tbsp chives", "notes": "4 x tbsp finely chopped chives", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 200.0, "unit": "gr", "item": "oz. corn", "notes": "200gr / 7 oz. sweet corn", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "juice of lemon", "notes": "Juice of 1 lemon", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "juice of lime", "notes": "Juice of 1 lime (About 2 x tbsps.)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 6.0, "unit": "leaves", "item": "lettuce leaf", "notes": "6 to 8 leaves of Chinese lettuce leaf, shredded", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "", "item": "limes", "notes": "2 x limes quartered.", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "", "item": "tbsp mayonnaise", "notes": "2 x tbsp good quality mayonnaise (or 2 x tbsp mayonnaise and 2 x tbsp natural yogurt – this will give a sharper result)", "category": "milk, eggs, other dairy"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "", "item": "tbsp japanese mirin", "notes": "4 x tbsp Japanese Mirin", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "olive oil", "notes": "1 x tbsp of olive oil", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "", "item": "salmon filets of 150gr / 5 oz. each", "notes": "4 x salmon filets of about 150gr / 5 oz. each", "category": "seafood"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "salt and pepper", "notes": "Salt and freshly ground black pepper", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "cut julienne", "notes": "1 x courgette (zucchini), shredded or cut julienne", "category": "cereal"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "tsp wasabi paste", "notes": "3 x tsp wasabi paste (more if you want more of a kick)", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "tbsp", "notes": "tbsp per person of wakame (Japanese Seaweed Salad)", "category": "?"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "to finish", "notes": "To Finish", "category": "?"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "to finish", "notes": "To Finish", "category": "?"}]'::jsonb, '["Bake the Salmon1.Pre-heat your oven to 200C / 400F.", "Place aluminium foil in a roasting tray. Use enough foil so that you can wrap the fish in it loosely.", "Place the fish on the foil.", "Drizzle over the oil and the lemon juice.", "Sprinkle over the salt and the pepper.3.Cover your fish with the foil, making a loose parcel.", "Place the tray in the oven and allow to bake for 7 to 12 minutes. The cooking time will not only depend on your oven, but also on how thick the salmon filets are. You can bake the salmon in advance as it should be served at room temperature.To Make the Coleslaw and Dressing", "Mix the dressing ingredients, except for the chives, together in a bowl. I find the best way to do this is with a metal whisk. Then stir in the chives. Check for flavouring and adjust if you wish. Set aside.", "Place the salad ingredients in a large salad bowl.3.When you are ready to serve pour over the dressing and toss through until evenly mixed.", "Serve with the salmon on the top of your salad and the spoonful of wakame on top of the salmon and a few slices of avocado and a wedge of lime on the side."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/TBR4BGWW/asian-coleslaw-with-baked-salmon', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/632822-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 1, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('kimchikimcheegimchi-korean-fermented-spicy-cabbage', 'Kimchi/Kimchee/Gimchi (Korean Fermented Spicy Cabbage)', 20, 0, 0, '{"calories": 223, "protein": 8.79, "carbs": 45.08, "fat": 6.94, "saturated_fat": 1.23, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 23899.01, "potassium": null, "fiber": 20.28, "sugar": 19.16, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 53.27, "calcium": 245.21, "iron": 9.26}'::jsonb, ARRAY['korean', 'asian', 'side dish', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'pescatarian', 'spoonacular', 'dessert', 'baking'], '[{"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "cup", "item": "brown sugar", "notes": "1 cup brown sugar, packed", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "napa cabbages", "notes": "•3 Napa cabbages", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "cups", "item": "coarse sea salt", "notes": "•4 cups coarse sea salt", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "fish sauce", "notes": "•1/2 cup fish sauce", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 12.0, "unit": "", "item": "garlic cloves", "notes": "•12 garlic cloves", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "ginger", "notes": "•2 tbsp minced ginger", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "cups", "item": "gochugaru", "notes": "•4 cups gochugaru (Korean red chili flakes)", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "green onions", "notes": "•3 green onions, cut into 2-inch pieces", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "cups", "item": "radish", "notes": "•2 cups radish (1/2 Korean radish), cut into matchstick pieces", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "rice flour", "notes": "•3 tbsp sweet rice flour (simmered with 3 cups water)", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "onion", "notes": "•1 yellow onion", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "saewujeot", "notes": "•4 tbsp saewujeot (salted shrimp)", "category": "?"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "saewujeot", "notes": "•4 tbsp saewujeot (salted shrimp)", "category": "?"}]'::jsonb, '["Remove discolored, bruised outer leaves of cabbage and rinse well under cold water.", "Cut cabbage head into desired pieces; smaller 2-inch pieces is recommended for easier access later.  In 3 separate large bowls, prepare one cup sea salt and water mixture for each bowl.", "Sprinkle remaining 1 cup of sea salt onto the leaves of the cabbages before soaking them in the salt water. Cabbages should be partially submerged in the salt water.", "Let sit for a minimum 6 hours but 12 hours is preferred.", "Once finished soaking, rinse the cabbage leaves thoroughly under cold water several times.", "Remove water from the cabbage by giving them a squeeze (they should have a rubbery texture by now) to remove excess water. Set in a colander or basket for at least 2 hours so the water will drain out thoroughly. Meanwhile, prepare the red pepper mixture to be mixed with cabbage leaves.", "Prepare 3 tbsp of the sweet rice flour with 3 cups of water into a small pot. Bring to a boil and whisk until the mixture turns into a glue-like consistency.", "Let cool and set aside.", "In a food processor, puree onion, garlic, ginger and some water until smooth.", "Pour gochugaru (chili flakes) in a large mixing bowl, add the garlic mixture puree, cooled rice glue, fish sauce, salted shrimp, sugar, and sesame seeds.", "Mix well and add the sliced radish and green onions.", "Lather each cabbage piece with red pepper mixture by rubbing them well (rubber gloves highly recommended). Continue until all the cabbage leaves are covered in the red pepper mixture. Pack them inside air-tight glass jars/containers.  Set out at room temperature for 2 days for fermentation to take place. After that, place in the refrigerator and serve as needed. The kimchi may keep for 2 or 3 months in the refrigerator.*Making kimchi is not easy, but if done right, the rewards are endless. You can take the easy way out and purchase them at your local Korean grocery store and even possibly in the Asian foods section of your local grocery."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/Z4R2DPPH/kimchi-kimchee-gimchi-korean-fermented-spicy-cabbage', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/648916-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 5, TRUE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
