teaspoon Onion powder", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tablespoon", "item": "paprika", "notes": "1 tablespoon Paprika", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 2.5, "unit": "teaspoons", "item": "salt", "notes": "2 1/2 teaspoons Salt", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 3.5, "unit": "lbs", "item": "chicken", "notes": "3.5 lbs chicken", "category": "meat"}]'::jsonb, '["Combine all seasonings. Seasoning mix is enough for 2 chickens. It may be made ahead and stored in an airtight container until needed.", "Place chicken in a 13- by 9- by 2-inch baking pan. Rub with half the seasoning mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight.Grill, covered, over medium coals, turning once, for 30 to 45 minutes or until juices run clear.This recipe yields 4 servings."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/6Y5FNTJW/blackened-cajun-chicken', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/635263-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('cajun-shrimp-and-marinated-cucumber-salad', 'Cajun Shrimp and Marinated Cucumber Salad', 2, 0, 0, '{"calories": 309, "protein": 16.54, "carbs": 11.09, "fat": 22.48, "saturated_fat": 3.12, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 1040.47, "potassium": null, "fiber": 1.02, "sugar": 5.26, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 6.69, "calcium": 88.39, "iron": 0.96}'::jsonb, ARRAY['cajun', 'creole', 'side dish', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'primal', 'fodmap friendly', 'whole 30', 'pescatarian', 'spoonacular', 'salad', 'baking'], '[{"quantity": 8.0, "unit": "ounces", "item": "shrimp", "notes": "8 ounces large uncooked shrimp, peeled with tails on (about 20), thawed", "category": "seafood"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "creole seasoning", "notes": "1 teaspoon Cajun or creole seasoning (like Tony Chachere''s), divided", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tablespoon", "item": "white/white wine vinegar", "notes": "1 tablespoon freshly squeezed lemon juice or white/white wine vinegar", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "cucumber", "notes": "1 whole English cucumber, sliced thinly", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "white wine vinegar", "notes": "2 tablespoons white wine vinegar (red wine vinegar also works well)", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "olive oil", "notes": "3 tablespoons olive oil, divided (optional)", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "pico de gallo", "notes": "1/4 cup prepared pico de gallo", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "salt and pepper", "notes": "salt and pepper to taste", "category": "spices and seasonings"}]'::jsonb, '["Preheat broiler to high.", "Place shrimp on a small rimmed baking sheet.", "Sprinkle with 1/2 tsp cajun seasoning, lemon juice (or vinegar), 1 T oil (if using) and pinch or two of salt and black pepper.", "Place in the oven on the upper third rack. Broil for 3-5 minutes until shrimp is completely opaque and pink.", "Meanwhile, place cucumber slices in a bowl and toss with remaining 1/2 tsp cajun seasoning, 2 T vinegar, 2 T olive oil (if using), and salt and pepper to taste.", "Divide cucumbers between two bowls, top each with half of the shrimp and a couple spoonfuls of pico de gallo."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/KYPLSPZQ/cajun-shrimp-and-marinated-cucumber-salad', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/636743-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('cajun-shrimp-chowder', 'Cajun Shrimp Chowder', 8, 0, 0, '{"calories": 180, "protein": 14.98, "carbs": 10.79, "fat": 9.51, "saturated_fat": 4.67, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 559.64, "potassium": null, "fiber": 2.31, "sugar": 4.38, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 11.17, "calcium": 68.71, "iron": 1.48}'::jsonb, ARRAY['cajun', 'creole', 'lunch', 'soup', 'main course', 'main dish', 'dinner', 'gluten free', 'spoonacular', 'breakfast'], '[{"quantity": 8.0, "unit": "ounces", "item": "asparagus spears", "notes": "8 ounces of Asparagus Spears, Cut into Thirds", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "slices", "item": "bacon", "notes": "3 slices of Bacon", "category": "meat"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "cups", "item": "seafood broth", "notes": "2 cups seafood broth", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tablespoon", "item": "cajun spice", "notes": "1 tablespoon of Cajun Spice", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "cup", "item": "corn", "notes": "1 cup of Corn", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "cloves", "item": "garlic", "notes": "3 cloves of garlic, crushed", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "heavy cream", "notes": "1/2 cup of Heavy Cream", "category": "milk, eggs, other dairy"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "lemon pepper", "notes": "1 teaspoon of Lemon Pepper", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "old bay seasoning", "notes": "1/2 teaspoon of Old Bay Seasoning", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "onion", "notes": "1 Small Onion, Chopped", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 8.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "salt and pepper", "notes": "Salt and Pepper to Taste", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "pound", "item": "shrimp", "notes": "1 pound Peeled and Cooked Shrimp", "category": "seafood"}, {"quantity": 14.5, "unit": "Oz", "item": "tomatoes", "notes": "14 1/2 Oz. Can of Diced Tomatoes", "category": "produce"}]'::jsonb, '["Grab up your frying pan and cook up the three strips of bacon. When they''re cooked up, pull them out, chop them up, and drain the bacon fat, reserving about a tablespoon. Turn your heat up to medium and add in your asparagus, onion, and garlic. Cook it up for 2 to 3 minutes.", "Add in the corn and tomatoes.", "Mix it together, give it a minute or two to warm up and then add in the broth, the chopped bacon and your spices; the old bay, cajun, lemon pepper, and salt and pepper to taste.", "Let the whole kit and kaboodle heat up for a good five minutes and then add in your cream.And last but most definitely not least, grab up your shrimp and pop them into the pan.Give the whole pan a swirl or two and allow the soup a couple minutes to heat back up.", "Serve with green onions sprinkled over the top."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/B5XRTYLQ/cajun-shrimp-chowda', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/636742-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('5-minute-rocky-road-fudge', '5-Minute Rocky Road Fudge', 15, 0, 0, '{"calories": 329, "protein": 5.48, "carbs": 36.39, "fat": 18.89, "saturated_fat": 7.32, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 63.58, "potassium": null, "fiber": 2.66, "sugar": 29.06, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 0.84, "calcium": 101.42, "iron": 1.89}'::jsonb, ARRAY['cajun', 'creole', 'gluten free', 'spoonacular', 'dessert', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "c", "item": "semi-sweet chocolate chips", "notes": "2 c. (12 oz. pkg.) semi-sweet chocolate chips", "category": "sweet snacks"}, {"quantity": 14.0, "unit": "oz", "item": "condensed milk", "notes": "14 oz. can sweetened condensed milk", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "t", "item": "vanilla extract", "notes": "1 t. vanilla extract", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 0.125, "unit": "t", "item": "salt", "notes": "1/8 t. salt", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "c", "item": "mini-marshmallows", "notes": "3 c. mini-marshmallows", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 1.5, "unit": "c", "item": "walnuts", "notes": "1 1/2 c. toasted, chopped walnuts", "category": "nuts"}]'::jsonb, '["Line a 13x9-inch pan with foil, lightly spray with cooking spray. Set aside.", "In a large, microwave safe bowl, add chocolate chips and condensed milk. Microwave for about 40 seconds, or until the chips are just melted when you stir them. If needed, continue to microwave in 15 second increments until melted. Do not overcook. Immediately stir in vanilla and salt. Then fold in the marshmallows and nuts.", "Working quickly, spread and press fudge into the prepared pan. Refrigerate until completely cooled before cutting into squares."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/HYGDSRK2/5-minute-rocky-road-fudge', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/631882-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('dulche-de-leche-fudge', 'Dulche De Leche Fudge', 16, 0, 0, '{"calories": 271, "protein": 3.73, "carbs": 28.46, "fat": 15.86, "saturated_fat": 9.41, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 34.8, "potassium": null, "fiber": 2.27, "sugar": 24.01, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 0, "calcium": 88.95, "iron": 1.84}'::jsonb, ARRAY['cajun', 'creole', 'dessert', 'gluten free', 'spoonacular', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "pound", "item": "semi-sweet chocolate", "notes": "1 pound good quality semi-sweet chocolate, roughly chopped", "category": "sweet snacks"}, {"quantity": 14.0, "unit": "ounce", "item": "condensed milk", "notes": "1 (14-ounce) can sweetened condensed milk", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "butter", "notes": "4 tablespoons unsalted butter", "category": "milk, eggs, other dairy"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tablespoon", "item": "vanilla extract", "notes": "1 tablespoon vanilla extract", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "cup", "item": "dulce de leche", "notes": "1 cup dulce de leche, heated slightly", "category": "baking"}]'::jsonb, '["Line an 8×8 baking square with parchment paper leaving overhang on both sides. Note: the easiest way to do this is to cut two strips of parchment paper and lay one across the other. Lightly spray with cooking spray and set aside.Fill the bottom of a double boiler or medium saucepan halfway with water, place over high heat and bring to a boil.", "Place the chopped chocolate, condensed milk, butter, and vanilla extract in the top of the double boiler or alternatively in a small saucepan and place on top of the hot water. Reduce the heat to low. Stir occasionally until all the chocolate has melted and the mixture is smooth.", "Remove form the heat and pour into the prepared pan. Using a rubber spatula, gently even out the chocolate mixture. Set aside.Gently warm the dulce de leche in the microwave for about 15-20 seconds until spreadable. Carefully pour the dulce de leche over the chocolate mixture. Using a tablespoon, make large swirls in the dulce de leche mixture so the bottom fudge layer is also visible.", "Place in the refrigerator and chill for at least 2 hours to set.Slice into small pieces to serve. Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator. Can be kept for 1 week."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/LJGKPR5Y/dulche-de-leche-fudge-for-valentine-s-day', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/1095942-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('bananas-foster', 'Bananas Foster', 1, 0, 0, '{"calories": 416, "protein": 1.47, "carbs": 56.83, "fat": 11.76, "saturated_fat": 7.33, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 98.3, "potassium": null, "fiber": 3.6, "sugar": 43.22, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 10.3, "calcium": 39.2, "iron": 0.57}'::jsonb, ARRAY['cajun', 'creole', 'dessert', 'gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'fodmap friendly', 'spoonacular', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "banana", "notes": "1 ripe banana", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "ounce", "item": "banana liqueur", "notes": "1/2 ounce banana liqueur", "category": "alcoholic beverages"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "brown sugar", "notes": "2 tablespoons brown sugar", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tablespoon", "item": "butter", "notes": "1 tablespoon butter", "category": "milk, eggs, other dairy"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "Dash", "item": "cinnamon", "notes": "Dash cinnamon", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "ounce", "item": "rum", "notes": "1 ounce white rum", "category": "alcoholic beverages"}]'::jsonb, '["Melt butter in chafing dish.", "Add sugar and blend well.", "Add banana and saute.", "Sprinkle cinnamon.", "Pour banana liqueur and rum over and ignite, basting banana with flaming liquid.", "Serve when flame dies out.", "Serves 1."]'::jsonb, 'http://www.foodista.com/recipe/GVRWW25K/bananas-foster', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/634229-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('french-quarter-bananas-foster-cupcakes', 'French Quarter Bananas Foster Cupcakes', 24, 0, 0, '{"calories": 215, "protein": 2.27, "carbs": 26.97, "fat": 11.01, "saturated_fat": 7.39, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 240.76, "potassium": null, "fiber": 1.07, "sugar": 16.97, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 1.58, "calcium": 31.15, "iron": 0.87}'::jsonb, ARRAY['cajun', 'creole', 'dessert', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'spoonacular', 'baking', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "teaspoons", "item": "baking powder", "notes": "2 teaspoons baking powder", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "bananas", "notes": "3 bananas, sliced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "brown sugar", "notes": "1/4 cup Brown sugar", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "cup", "item": "butter", "notes": "cup unsalted butter", "category": "milk, eggs, other dairy"}, {"quantity": 0.75, "unit": "cup", "item": "coconut", "notes": "3/4 cup shredded coconut, lightly toasted", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "eggs", "notes": "3 eggs", "category": "milk, eggs, other dairy"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "cups", "item": "flour", "notes": "2 cups all-purpose flour", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "ground cinnamon", "notes": "1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "rum", "notes": "1/4 cup rum", "category": "alcoholic beverages"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "teaspoons", "item": "salt", "notes": "2 teaspoons Salt", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.5, "unit": "cups", "item": "sugar", "notes": "1 1/2 cups sugar", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 0.75, "unit": "cup", "item": "coconut milk", "notes": "3/4 cup unsweetened coconut milk", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "vanilla", "notes": "1/2 teaspoon vanilla", "category": "baking"}]'::jsonb, '["Add sugar, about 1/4 cup at a time, beating until combined.", "Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla. Alternately add flour mixture and coconut milk to butter mixture, beating on low speed after each addition just until combined. Fold in the 3/4 cup coconut and the rum.Spoon batter into prepared cups, filling each about 3/4 full. Use the back of a spoon to smooth out batter in cups.", "Bake about 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in centers comes out clean. Cool cupcakes in muffin cups on wire racks for 5 minutes.", "Remove cupcakes from muffin cups. Cool completely on wire racks.Spoon Bananas Foster Topping onto cupcakes. If desired, pipe whipped cream onto cupcakes and sprinkle with additional coconut.Directions for Bananas Foster Topping:In a large skillet melt 1/3 cup butter over medium heat. Stir in 1/2 cup packed brown sugar, 1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon.", "Add 3 bananas, sliced; toss gently to coat. Cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes or until bananas are heated through. Meanwhile, in a small saucepan heat 1/4 cup rum over low heat just until rum almost simmers; remove from heat. If desired, use a long match to carefully ignite the rum.* Once the flame dies down, pour rum into banana mixture.For safety, keep face and hands away from ignited rum in saucepan. The blue flame is hard to see."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/Z2W8FM5Y/french-quarter-bananas-foster-cupcakes', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/643385-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = E