her in a small bowl.Spray cookie sheet with olive oil cooking spray.", "Place potatoes on cookie sheet. Toss with olive oil.", "Sprinkle spice mixture over potatoes and toss.Cook for 25 minutes. Flip over and cook for another 5 minutes."]'::jsonb, 'http://www.foodista.com/recipe/4VZ36NKT/cajun-potato-wedges', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/636733-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('asparagus-and-pea-soup-real-convenience-food', 'Asparagus and Pea Soup: Real Convenience Food', 2, 0, 0, '{"calories": 217, "protein": 10.84, "carbs": 28.83, "fat": 7.76, "saturated_fat": 1.13, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 11.26, "potassium": null, "fiber": 11.17, "sugar": 11.54, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 67.3, "calcium": 75.19, "iron": 4.7}'::jsonb, ARRAY['antipasti', 'soup', 'starter', 'snack', 'appetizer', 'antipasto', 'hor d''oeuvre', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'vegan', 'spoonacular', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "bag", "item": "asparagus", "notes": "1 bag of frozen organic asparagus (preferably thawed)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "T", "item": "evoo", "notes": "1T EVOO (extra virgin olive oil)", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "cloves", "item": "garlic", "notes": "a couple of garlic cloves", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "", "item": "onion", "notes": "1/2 onion", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "c", "item": "peas", "notes": "2-3c of frozen organic peas", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "box", "item": "vegetable broth", "notes": "1 box low-sodium vegetable broth", "category": "canned and jarred"}]'::jsonb, '["Chop the garlic and onions.", "Saute the onions in the EVOO, adding the garlic after a couple of minutes; cook until the onions are translucent.", "Add the whole bag of asparagus and cover everything with the broth. Season with salt and pepper and a pinch of red pepper flakes, if using.Simmer until the asparagus is bright green and tender (if you''ve thawed the asparagus it will only take a couple of minutes). Turn off the heat and puree using an immersion blender.", "Add peas (the heat of the soup will quickly thaw them) and puree until smooth; add more until it reaches the thickness you like.Top with chives and a small dollop of creme fraiche or sour cream or greek yogurt."]'::jsonb, 'https://fullbellysisters.blogspot.com/2011/03/asparagus-and-pea-soup-real-convenience.html', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/716406-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('easy-to-make-spring-rolls', 'Easy To Make Spring Rolls', 4, 0, 0, '{"calories": 161, "protein": 13.32, "carbs": 28.28, "fat": 2.0, "saturated_fat": 0.14, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 1245.15, "potassium": null, "fiber": 5.84, "sugar": 9.93, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 285.51, "calcium": 432.33, "iron": 14.19}'::jsonb, ARRAY['vietnamese', 'asian', 'fingerfood', 'antipasti', 'starter', 'snack', 'appetizer', 'antipasto', 'hor d''oeuvre', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'pescatarian', 'spoonacular', 'dessert', 'salad'], '[{"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "you can use regular basil", "notes": "1/2 cup Thai basil or you can use regular basil", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "small head", "item": "boston lettuce", "notes": "small head of Boston lettuce, roughly chopped", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "small", "item": "chili pepper", "notes": "small chili pepper, finely chopped", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "fish sauce", "notes": "1/4 cup fish sauce", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "coriander leaves", "notes": "1/2 cup coriander (cilantro) leaves", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "clove", "item": "garlic", "notes": "1 clove garlic", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "lime juice", "notes": "2 tablespoons fresh lime juice", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "mint leaves", "notes": "1/2 cup mint leaves", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "bell pepper", "notes": "red bell pepper, thinly sliced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "rice vinegar", "notes": "1/4 cup rice vinegar", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 8.0, "unit": "large", "item": "shrimp", "notes": "8 large cooked shrimp, slice in half lengthways", "category": "seafood"}, {"quantity": 8.0, "unit": "8-inch", "item": "spring roll wrappers", "notes": "8 large (8-inch) spring roll wrappers", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tablespoon", "item": "sugar", "notes": "1 tablespoon sugar", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "water", "notes": "1/4 cup water", "category": "beverages"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "nuoc cham", "notes": "Nuoc Cham (dipping sauce)", "category": "?"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "nuoc cham", "notes": "Nuoc Cham (dipping sauce)", "category": "?"}]'::jsonb, '["Have all the ingredients ready for assembly. In a large bowl filled with water, dip a wrapper in the water. The rice wrapper will begin to soften and this is your cue to remove it from the water and lay it flat.", "Place 2 shrimp halves in a row across the center and top with basil, mint, cilantro and lettuce. Leave about 1 to 2 inches uncovered on each side.  Fold uncovered sides inward, then tightly roll the wrapper, beginning at the end with the lettuce.  Repeat with remaining wrappers and ingredients.", "Cut and serve at room temperature with dipping sauce.The Culinary Chases Note: The rice wrapper can be fussy to handle if you let it soak too long. I usually give it a couple of swishes in the water and then remove. It may feel slightly stiff but by the time you are ready to roll up, the wrapper will become very pliable.  A typical spring roll contains cooked rice vermicelli, slivers of cooked pork and julienned carrots but you can use whatever suits your fancy.  Enjoy!"]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/B5HHJWNP/easy-to-make-spring-rolls', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/642129-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
