oil, vinegar, season with salt and pepper", "Mix well and leave in the refrigerator for 1 / 2 hour", "This salad is left to eat alone or to accompany meat and poultry dishes, enjoy ..."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/TTBNDB7Q/lentill-mango-salad', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/649944-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('shrimp-and-avocado-salad', 'Shrimp and Avocado Salad', 4, 0, 0, '{"calories": 639, "protein": 33.99, "carbs": 53.29, "fat": 37.05, "saturated_fat": 5.36, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 378.39, "potassium": null, "fiber": 17.27, "sugar": 20.01, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 115.99, "calcium": 143.54, "iron": 3.97}'::jsonb, ARRAY['side dish', 'lunch', 'main course', 'salad', 'main dish', 'dinner', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'pescatarian', 'spoonacular'], '[{"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "the shrimp", "notes": "The Shrimp", "category": "seafood"}, {"quantity": 600.0, "unit": "gr", "item": "shrimp", "notes": "About 600gr of large tiger style shrimp (prawns/langoustine) peeled and cleaned", "category": "seafood"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "", "item": "garlic cloves", "notes": "2 x garlic cloves, crushed", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "olive oil", "notes": "1 x tbsp olive oil", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "juice of lime", "notes": "Juice of 1 lime", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "salt and pepper", "notes": "Salt and Pepper", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "the salad", "notes": "The Salad", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "leaves", "item": "the of 1 cos lettuce", "notes": "The leaves of 1 medium Cos lettuce finely shredded", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.75, "unit": "", "item": "basil leaves", "notes": "6/8 basil leaves chopped", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 200.0, "unit": "gr", "item": "corn", "notes": "200gr sweet corn", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "spring onions", "notes": "3 x spring onions (scallions) chopped finely", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 600.0, "unit": "gr", "item": "pineapple", "notes": "600gr fresh pineapple cut into small cubes", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "", "item": "avocados into cubes", "notes": "2 x avocados chopped into cubes", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "avocado", "notes": "Avocado", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "the dressing", "notes": "The Dressing", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "tbsp olive oil", "notes": "3 x tbsp olive oil", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "tbsp honey", "notes": "3 x tbsp honey", "category": "nut butters, jams, and honey"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "juice of lime", "notes": "Juice and zest of 3 limes", "category": "produce"}]'::jsonb, '["Firstly, to cook the shrimp, heat the olive oil in a pan and once hot add the shrimp crushed garlic and chili flakes. It is important to get the oil nice and hot (not smoking, just before that point) your shrimp should sizzle when added to the pan. Check the back of the shrimp and when you see the colour change about half way up, turn them over. Do the same on the other side. This should only take a minute to two minutes maximum on both sides  otherwise you will get a rubbery result if you leave it too long. Squeeze over the lime juice  this too should bubble and reduce.", "Add a little salt and pepper, stir through, remove from the heat and set aside.", "Mix the dressing ingredients together, check for flavour, adjust if need be and set aside.", "Place all the salad ingredients in a bowl except the avocado and the salt and pepper. Prepare the avocado as you are about to serve otherwise it will turn brown. Once it is covered in the lime dressing, this will slow down the oxidization process and it wont go brown so easily.", "When you are ready to serve mix  of the avocado through the salad and add the dressing. Toss everything together. Taste to see if you need any salt and pepper.", "Place your shrimp on top of the salad with the rest of the avocado and sprinkle/pour any residue from the pan over your salad in which you cooked the shrimp. This is great flavour, so you dont want to lose it."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/ZTNWCWQP/shrimp-and-avocado-salad', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/659927-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('salmon-watercress-fennel-and-baby-beetroot-salad-with-lemony-caviar-dressing', 'Salmon, Watercress, Fennel and Baby Beetroot Salad With Lemony "Caviar" Dressing', 4, 0, 0, '{"calories": 440, "protein": 27.23, "carbs": 18.51, "fat": 29.1, "saturated_fat": 4.24, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 186.03, "potassium": null, "fiber": 5.58, "sugar": 10.85, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 20.94, "calcium": 109.2, "iron": 3.56}'::jsonb, ARRAY['side dish', 'lunch', 'main course', 'salad', 'main dish', 'dinner', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'primal', 'pescatarian', 'spoonacular'], '[{"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "teaspoons", "item": "arënkha msc caviar substitute", "notes": "4 teaspoons Arënkha MSC caviar substitute", "category": "gourmet"}, {"quantity": 12.0, "unit": "", "item": "baby beets", "notes": "12 cooked baby beets", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "bay leaf", "notes": "1 bay leaf", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "pepper", "notes": "freshly ground black pepper", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 6.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "extra virgin olive oil", "notes": "6 tbsp extra virgin olive oil", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "head", "item": "fennel", "notes": "1 head fennel, outside leaves discarded, finely sliced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "lemon juice", "notes": "2 tbsp lemon juice", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 16.0, "unit": "oz", "item": "salmon fillets", "notes": "4 110g (4oz) skinless salmon fillets", "category": "seafood"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "tarragon stalks", "notes": "tarragon stalks", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 9.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "tarragon leaves", "notes": "few tarragon leaves", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "bunch", "item": "watercress", "notes": "1 bunch watercress, picked over, washed & dried", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tablespoon", "item": "white wine", "notes": "1 tablespoon white wine", "category": "alcoholic beverages"}]'::jsonb, '["Place the salmon in a pan, cover with water, and add the wine, bay and tarragon stalks.  Bring to the boil and then immediately turn off and leave for a couple of minutes to cook in the residual heat.", "Remove to a plate with a slotted spoon and leave to cool before flaking into large pieces.Make the dressing by lightly whisking the olive oil and lemon juice together. Stir in the Arnkha MSC and season with some black pepper.Next, arrange the watercress, beets and fennel in 4 shallow salad bowls, then add the salmon and tarragon.", "Drizzle over the Arnkha MSC dressing and serve."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/WHSTLX2T/salmon-watercress-fennel-and-baby-beetroot-salad-with-lemony-arenkha-msc-dressing', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/659143-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('winter-fattoush-salad', 'Winter Fattoush Salad', 6, 0, 0, '{"calories": 345, "protein": 17.39, "carbs": 49.67, "fat": 9.43, "saturated_fat": 1.97, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 601.87, "potassium": null, "fiber": 18.6, "sugar": 4.89, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 45.18, "calcium": 149.56, "iron": 5.69}'::jsonb, ARRAY['middle eastern', 'side dish', 'lunch', 'main course', 'salad', 'main dish', 'dinner', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'spoonacular', 'baking', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "agave nectar", "notes": "1 teaspoon agave nectar", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "feta cheese", "notes": "1/4 cup feta cheese (optional)", "category": "cheese"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "flat leaf parsley leaves", "notes": "½ cup flat leaf parsley leaves (or a mix of parsley and mint)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "cloves", "item": "garlic", "notes": "2 cloves garlic, minced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "ground sumac", "notes": "½ teaspoon ground sumac", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "kosher salt", "notes": "1 teaspoon kosher salt", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "", "item": "lacinato kale leaves", "notes": "4 fresh Lacinato kale leaves", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "lemon juice", "notes": "2 tablespoons lemon juice", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.5, "unit": "cups", "item": "lentils", "notes": "1½ cups cooked lentils (many markets carry vacuum-packed, precooked lentils, or boil 1 cup dried brown lentils in 2 cups salted water until tender, then drain)", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "olive oil", "notes": "3 tablespoons olive oil", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "small", "item": "onion", "notes": "1 small onion, coarsely chopped", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tablespoon", "item": "parsley", "notes": "1 tablespoon minced parsley", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "large", "item": "persian cucumber", "notes": "1 large organic English or Persian cucumber with skin (about 1 cup shredded)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "large", "item": "pita breads", "notes": "2 large pita breads", "category": "bakery/bread"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "small bunch", "item": "radishes", "notes": "1 small bunch red radishes or other varietals such as watermelon or daikon (about ½ cup, shredded)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 6.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "salt and pepper", "notes": "Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "small head", "item": "savoy cabbage", "notes": "1 small head savoy cabbage (about 2 heaping cups, shredded)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tablespoon", "item": "za''atar", "notes": "1 tablespoon za''atar", "category": "ethnic foods"}]'::jsonb, '["Toast the pita: Preheat the oven to 350F.", "Whisk the oil, zaatar and salt in a small bowl.", "Lay the pita bread on a baking sheet and brush both sides with the oil.", "Saute the onions and oil in a small skillet until onions soften and begin to brown.", "Add the lentils and stir to blend. Stir in the garlic and parsley and remove from heat. Season with salt and pepper.", "Whisk the dressing ingredients in a bowl until fully combined. You can also use a handheld blender.Compose the salad: Toss the salad ingredients in a large bowl.", "Add the lentils and pita crisps.", "Drizzle with the dressing and toss again. Mound the salad on a serving platter. Top with feta cheese and sprinkle with sumac."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/FWQFYDLT/winter-fattoush-salad', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/665378-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('butternut-squash-tofu-salad-with-toasted-hazelnuts', 'Butternut Squash Tofu Salad With Toasted Hazelnuts', 4, 0, 0, '{"calories": 260, "protein": 12.82, "carbs": 31.92, "fat": 11.49, "saturated_fat": 1.63, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 269.38, "potassium": null, "fiber": 6.52, "sugar": 6.95, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 78.85, "calcium": 144.58, "iron": 3.43}'::jsonb, ARRAY['side dish', 'lunch', 'main course', 'salad', 'main dish', 'dinner', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan', 'spoonacular', 'baking', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "tsp", "item": "pepper", "notes": "½ tsp black pepper", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "butternut squash", "notes": "1 whole butternut squash, peeled and cut into ½ inch cubes (about 3 cups chopped)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 14.0, "unit": "oz", "item": "extra tofu", "notes": "14 oz extra firm tofu", "category": "refrigerated"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "tsp", "item": "lemon juice", "notes": "¼ tsp lemon juice", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "hazel nuts", "notes": "½ cup raw hazel nuts", "category": "nuts"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "bell pepper", "notes": "1 whole red pepper (chopped)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "", "item": "onions", "notes": "½ whole red onions (finely sliced)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tsp", "item": "rosemary leaves", "notes": "1 tsp rosemary leaves", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "salt", "notes": "Salt to taste", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "water", "notes": "½ cup water", "category": "beverages"}]'::jsonb, '["Preheat oven at 370 degree Fahrenheit. Prepare 2 cookie sheets with a liner/parchment paper.In one cookie sheet spread the tofu pieces and in another cookie sheet spread the hazelnuts.", "Put the cookie sheets in the oven and bake.", "Bake hazelnuts for 5-7 minutes and tofu for 20 minutes.In the meantime combine water and squash in a saucepan. Cover and boil for 5 minutes or until the squash pieces are soft.When the squash is boiled let it cool for a while and grind into a smooth paste.In a bowl combine salt, black pepper, rosemary, lemon juice and  squash puree and keep it aside.When the hazelnuts are done take it out of the oven and let the tofu cook in the same oven.", "Let the nuts cool and rub gently between palms or with paper towel to remove the skin.Once the tofu is cooked for 20 minutes or until very light golden brown in color take it out from the oven.In salad bowl combine all the ingredients and mix gently so that the tofu retains its shape.", "Garnish with more hazelnuts and/or rosemary and serve immediately.This salad tastes great when warm but can be served at room temperature also."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/ZXS8QYZ6/butternut-squash-tofu-salad-with-toasted-hazelnuts', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/636604-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
