or apple cider vinegar", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}]'::jsonb, '["First, chop the iceberg lettuce and place in a large bowl.Wash and dice the tomatoes, cucumber, green peppers, and carrot into pieces.Ad them to the bowl with chopped lettuce.Prepare quinoa according to package instructions.", "Add the cooked quinoa to the salad bowl.Season with some salt and black pepper.Next, add the olive tapenade, vinegar, and extra virgin olive oil to the bowl and to stir everything very well.", "Serve."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/GF3WXNG2/quinoa-salad-with-summer-veggies', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/1095791-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('mung-bean-sprout-and-quinoa-salad', 'Mung Bean Sprout and Quinoa Salad', 6, 0, 0, '{"calories": 355, "protein": 16.63, "carbs": 50.21, "fat": 11.3, "saturated_fat": 8.07, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 233.59, "potassium": null, "fiber": 11.86, "sugar": 6.03, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 34.02, "calcium": 127.16, "iron": 5.82}'::jsonb, ARRAY['side dish', 'lunch', 'main course', 'salad', 'main dish', 'dinner', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan', 'spoonacular', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "bragg''s all natural apple cider vinegar", "notes": "4 tablespoons of Bragg''s all natural apple cider vinegar (raw)", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "pinch", "item": "of basil", "notes": "2 pinchs of dried basil", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "bell peppers", "notes": "1/2 cup of bell peppers (diced)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "coconut oil", "notes": "4 tablespoons of cold pressed coconut oil", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "cups", "item": "quinoa", "notes": "2 cups cooked quinoa", "category": "pasta and rice"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "pinch", "item": "cilantro", "notes": "1 pinch of dried cilantro (optional)", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "clove", "item": "garlic", "notes": "1 clove of garlic (minced)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.5, "unit": "cups", "item": "sprouted mung beans", "notes": "1 1/2 cups of sprouted mung beans", "category": "health foods"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "onions", "notes": "1/4 cup of of red onions (diced)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "pinch", "item": "of oregano", "notes": "3 pinchs of dried oregano", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 6.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "salt and pepper", "notes": "salt and pepper to taste", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 6.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "spinach", "notes": "spinach", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "medium", "item": "tomatoes", "notes": "2 medium tomatoes (diced)", "category": "produce"}]'::jsonb, '["First you sprout!Soak mung beans over night in a jar covered with cheese cloth.  Note: use rubber band to keep cheese cloth in place.Rinse and pour out all of the water from the soaked mung beans.Then place jar diagonally in a bowl, like picture below.Wash mung beans 2 times a day.  You can have them grow 1 to 2 inches in lengthbut, I just kept them short.  I just let it sit for a little bit more than 1.5 days.It is ready to eat after washing.Prepare sprouts", "Cook quinoa", "Steam. corn", "Prepare veggies (mince, slice, and dice)", "Place quinoa and prepared veggies in a bowl and mix in dressing.  Then, place over a bed of spinach.Top off with corn (optional)Enjoy!"]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/WFDCWVHF/mung-bean-sprout-and-quinoa-salad', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/652594-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('red-quinoa-and-roasted-cauliflower-salad', 'Red Quinoa and Roasted Cauliflower Salad', 4, 0, 0, '{"calories": 444, "protein": 12.84, "carbs": 44.68, "fat": 26.19, "saturated_fat": 4.7, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 386.4, "potassium": null, "fiber": 8.18, "sugar": 8.25, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 89.29, "calcium": 144.94, "iron": 3.68}'::jsonb, ARRAY['side dish', 'lunch', 'main course', 'salad', 'main dish', 'dinner', 'gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'spoonacular', 'baking', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "medium", "item": "cauliflower", "notes": "1 medium cauliflower", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "cup", "item": "quinoa", "notes": "1 cup red quinoa", "category": "pasta and rice"}, {"quantity": 0.33333334, "unit": "cup", "item": "walnuts", "notes": "1/3 cup walnuts, chopped", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "apricots", "notes": "1/4 cup dried apricots", "category": "dried fruits"}, {"quantity": 0.33333334, "unit": "cup", "item": "feta cheese", "notes": "1/3 cup feta cheese", "category": "cheese"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "green onions", "notes": "3 green onions, thinly sliced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "Tbsp", "item": "parsley", "notes": "3 Tbsp. chopped parsley", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "salt and pepper", "notes": "Salt and Pepper to taste", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "lemon", "notes": "1 lemon", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "olive oil", "notes": "Olive oil", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}]'::jsonb, '["Cook the quinoa according to package directions.", "Preheat the oven to 400 F", "Cut head of cauliflower into florets.  Toss with olive oil, salt and pepper and place on a baking sheet.  Roast cauliflower for 20 minutes or until tender.", "Meanwhile, crumble the cheese and chop the rest of the ingredients.", "Mix them all together, sprinkle with some extra virgin olive oil and juice from 1/2 a lemon season to taste.", "Serve warm or cold."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/22QVP2CY/red-quinoa-and-cauliflower-salad', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/658087-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('cracked-wheat-salad-with-dates-tahini-yogurt', 'Cracked Wheat Salad with Dates & Tahini Yogurt', 2, 0, 0, '{"calories": 890, "protein": 32.03, "carbs": 100.97, "fat": 47.93, "saturated_fat": 6.24, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 55.65, "potassium": null, "fiber": 21.0, "sugar": 18.05, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 56.18, "calcium": 299.26, "iron": 10.4}'::jsonb, ARRAY['side dish', 'lunch', 'main course', 'salad', 'main dish', 'dinner', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'spoonacular', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "lentils", "notes": "1/2 cup red lentils, cooked", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "cup", "item": "cracked wheat", "notes": "1 cup cracked wheat, cooked", "category": "health foods"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "dates", "notes": "1/4 cup dates, chopped", "category": "dried fruits"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "Tbs", "item": "extra virgin olive oil", "notes": "1 Tbs extra virgin olive oil", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "parsley", "notes": "1/2 cup fresh parsley, chopped", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "greek yogurt", "notes": "1/2 cup greek yogurt", "category": "milk, eggs, other dairy"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tsp", "item": "ground coriander", "notes": "1 tsp ground coriander", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tsp", "item": "ground cumin", "notes": "1 tsp ground cumin", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "lemon", "notes": "1 lemon", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "small", "item": "onion", "notes": "1 small red onion, finely chopped", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "sesame seeds", "notes": "sesame seeds", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tsp", "item": "paprika", "notes": "1 tsp sweet paprika", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "tahini", "notes": "1/2 cup tahini", "category": "health foods"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "medium", "item": "zucchini", "notes": "1 medium zucchini, diced and grilled in some olive oil", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}]'::jsonb, '["For Tahini Yogurt: dry roast ground cumin and coriander in a pan for a few minutes until they start getting fragrant. In a mixing bowl, add yogurt and tahini and mix well. Now add cumin, coriander, juice and zest of 1 lemon, olive oil, and salt to taste and mix well to form a thick paste-like mixture. Set aside.For Assembling the Salad: In a big salad bowl mix everything and season with little salt (just be careful as the yogurt topping also has salt in it).", "Serve in individual salad bowls,  putting a dollop of the tahini yogurt and sprinkling some toasted sesame seeds. Tastes best at room temperature."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/6PVSJLCP/cracked-wheat-salad-with-dates-tahini-yogrt', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/640338-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('okra-tomato-salad', 'Okra Tomato Salad', 1, 0, 0, '{"calories": 100, "protein": 4.12, "carbs": 21.51, "fat": 0.6, "saturated_fat": 0.08, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 218.71, "potassium": null, "fiber": 6.05, "sugar": 11.35, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 52.8, "calcium": 128.01, "iron": 1.51}'::jsonb, ARRAY['side dish', 'antipasti', 'salad', 'starter', 'snack', 'appetizer', 'antipasto', 'hor d''oeuvre', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'whole 30', 'vegan', 'spoonacular', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 10.0, "unit": "", "item": "two-inch long okra pods", "notes": "10-15 two-inch long okra pods", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "large", "item": "tomato", "notes": "1 large tomato, chopped", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "serving", "item": "salt and pepper", "notes": "Salt and Pepper to taste", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "leaves", "item": "basil", "notes": "3 leaves of basil, finely diced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "balsamic vinegar", "notes": "2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}]'::jsonb, '["Remove ends of okra pods, discard. Slice okra.", "Place okra in a basket and steam for five to seven minutes.", "Roughly chop a tomato.", "When okra is cooked, place in a bowl and toss with tomato.", "Season with salt and pepper.", "In a small bowl whisk basil into balsamic vinegar.", "Drizzle over okra and tomato."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/XNX4G5JC/the-essence-of-okra', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/653549-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('quinoa-salad-with-avocado-asparagus-and-sun-dried-tomatoes', 'Quinoa Salad With Avocado, Asparagus and Sun Dried Tomatoes', 2, 0, 0, '{"calories": 717, "protein": 20.33, "carbs": 89.88, "fat": 35.0, "saturated_fat": 4.86, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 627.75, "potassium": null, "fiber": 19.38, "sugar": 16.24, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 30.43, "calcium": 150.64, "iron": 9.69}'::jsonb, ARRAY['side dish', 'lunch', 'main course', 'salad', 'main dish', 'dinner', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'spoonacular', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "cup", "item": "asparagus", "notes": "1 cup asparagus cut into few inch pieces", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "avocado", "notes": "1 avocado", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "garlic clove", "notes": "1 garlic clove minced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "honey", "notes": "1/2 teaspoon honey or agave", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "", "item": "juice of lemon", "notes": "1/2 Juice of lemon", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "olive oil", "notes": "2 tablespoons olive oil", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "cup", "item": "quinoa", "notes": "1 cup quinoa", "category": "pasta and rice"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "salt", "notes": "1/2 teaspoon salt", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "herb seasoning", "notes": "1 teaspoon Italian herb seasoning", "category": "other"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "", "item": "shallots", "notes": "2 shallots", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "sun tomatoes", "notes": "1/2 cup sun dried tomatoes", "category": "canned and jarred"}]'::jsonb, '["Rinse quinoa under cold running water for a minute or two to get rid of the bitter aftertaste.", "Transfer to a pot or rice cooker, add 2 cups of water, salt, cover and bring to a boil. Lower down the heat and cook 15 min or until water is absorbed.In another pot bring water to a boil, add asparagus and simmer 5-8 min or until soft.When ready cool down the quinoa and asparagus. Meanwhile chop all the veggie ingredients.Prepare the dressing by simply mixing all of its ingredients (lemon juice, 2 tbs olive oil, 1 garlic clove, 1 tsp italian seasoning, 1/2 tsp honey, pinch of salt) in a bowl.In a bowl combine quinoa, avocado, asparagus, sun dried tomatoes and shallots.", "Pour the dressing and mix until all is combined."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/NRZZ4FGK/quinoa-salad-with-avocado-asparagus-and-sun-dried-tomatoes', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/657679-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('summer-kale-orange-pomegranate-salad-with-moscato-dressing', 'Summer Kale, Orange & Pomegranate Salad with Moscato Dressing', 4, 0, 0, '{"calories": 164, "protein": 3.68, "carbs": 13.9, "fat": 10.21, "saturated_fat": 1.19, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 26.8, "potassium": null, "fiber": 3.65, "sugar": 7.13, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 77.58, "calcium": 90.39, "iron": 1.58}'::jsonb, ARRAY['side dish', 'antipasti', 'salad', 'starter', 'snack', 'appetizer', 'antipasto', 'hor d''oeuvre', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan', 'spoonacular', 'vegetarian'], '[{"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "head", "item": "butter lettuce", "notes": "1/2 head of butter lettuce, cored & chopped", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "dijon mustard", "notes": "1/2 teaspoon Dijon Mustard", "category": "condiments"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "item": "extra virgin olive oil", "notes": "1/2 cup extra virgin olive oil", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "ground pepper", "notes": "1/2 teaspoon ground black pepper", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "bunch", "item": "dinosaur kale", "notes": "1/2 bunch dinosaur kale, thick stems removed & leaves thinly sliced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 6.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "presto moscato dolce", "notes": "6 tablespoons Presto Moscato Dolce", "category": "alcoholic beverages"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "orange juice", "notes": "3 tablespoons freshly squeezed orange juice", "category": "beverages"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "to 2 oranges", "notes": "1 to 2 oranges, peeled & segmented", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "curley parsley", "notes": "1/4 cup curley parsley, chopped", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "garnish: pomegranate molasses", "notes": "Garnish: Pomegranate molasses, Fresh pomegranate seeds", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "", "item": "bell pepper", "notes": "1/2 red bell pepper, thinly sliced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "cup", "item": "cabbage", "notes": "1 cup shredded red cabbage", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "small", "item": "onion", "notes": "1/2 small red onion, thinly sliced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "item": "sunflower seeds", "notes": "1/4 cup sunflower seeds, lightly toasted", "category": "savory snacks"}]'::jsonb, '["Assemble the Salad: Over medium heat, toast sunflower seeds in a small skillet until lightly golden; Cool.In a large bowl, combine kale, parsley, butter lettuce,  cabbage, orange segments, onion, bell pepper & sunflower seeds.Season with Kosher salt & fresh cracked black pepper to taste.In a small bowl, whisk together all the dressing ingredients & lightly spoon dressing over kale mixture to lightly coat.Plating: On a chilled serving plate, place a 3 x 4 metal plating/forming ring;  Spoon kale salad mixture into the ring & lightly pressing down to compact salad;", "Place 2 orange segments on top.Carefully remove plating ring.", "Sprinkle fresh pomegranate seeds around the plate with a quarter size drop of pomegranate molasses.", "Serve immediately or refrigerate for up to 2 days."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/GBVC4L73/summer-kale-orange-pomegranate-salad-with-moscato-dressing', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/662231-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
