"notes": "Kkikkoman soy sauce", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tablespoon", "item": "cooking wine", "notes": "1 tablespoon Cooking wine", "category": "alcoholic beverages"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "oz", "item": "gy a wrappers", "notes": "Gyoza wrappers", "category": "ethnic foods"}]'::jsonb, '["Chop cabbage fine, place in colander and pour boiling water over the cabbage. Cool to touch, then squeeze cabbage well to get the water out. In a bowl mix cabbage, chopped green onions, chopped mushrooms and grated ginger.", "Mix ground beef, wine, soy sauce, sesame oil and black pepper together with vegetables; mix well.", "Place a small amount of filling (about 1 teaspoon) in center of gyoza wrapping and fold in half. Pleat edge to seal. If edges won''t stick together, dampen the inside edge with a little water, then pleat. Put 2 tablespoon salad oil in Then, at edge of pan, pour in a little water, up to 1/4 of the depth of the pot-stickers. Cover, turn heat to low and simmer until water is gone.", "Mix soy sauce with chili sesame oil. Use a proportion of 10 parts soy sauce to 1 part oil; if you use a 5 to 1 proportion it may be a little hot for most people. The authentic sauce is a 2 to 1 proportion."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/VVK5NQ7C/japanese-gyoza-pot-stickers', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/648475-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('taco-egg-roll', 'Taco Egg Roll', 8, 0, 0, '{"calories": 190, "protein": 11.04, "carbs": 9.99, "fat": 11.57, "saturated_fat": 4.41, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 466.08, "potassium": null, "fiber": 1.06, "sugar": 0.82, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 1.97, "calcium": 17.14, "iron": 1.83}'::jsonb, ARRAY['chinese', 'asian', 'antipasti', 'starter', 'snack', 'appetizer', 'antipasto', 'hor d''oeuvre', 'spoonacular', 'baking'], '[{"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "lb", "item": "ground beef", "notes": "1 lb ground beef, turkey, or chicken", "category": "meat"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "package", "item": "taco seasoning", "notes": "1 package taco seasoning", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 8.0, "unit": "", "item": "egg roll wrappers", "notes": "8-10 egg roll wrappers", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "package", "item": "mexican cheese", "notes": "1 package Mexican shredded cheese", "category": "cheese"}]'::jsonb, '["Brown and drain ground beef.", "Season according to taco seasoning instructions.", "Turn off heat, and mix in shredded cheese with taco meat.", "Fill egg roll wrappers.", "Brush egg rolls with olive oil.", "Bake at 375 for 15 minutes, flipping egg rolls at 8 minutes.", "Serve hot with sour cream!", "Experiment with these things!", "Add peppers, rice, or refried beans. Make them your own."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/MH35XSK3/taco-egg-roll', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/662744-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('chinese-potstickers', 'Chinese Potstickers', 24, 0, 0, '{"calories": 135, "protein": 4.25, "carbs": 18.27, "fat": 4.74, "saturated_fat": 1.11, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 243.78, "potassium": null, "fiber": 0.75, "sugar": 0.37, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 0, "calcium": 12.78, "iron": 1.17}'::jsonb, ARRAY['chinese', 'asian', 'antipasti', 'starter', 'snack', 'appetizer', 'antipasto', 'hor d''oeuvre', 'dairy free', 'spoonacular', 'dessert', 'baking'], '[{"quantity": 200.0, "unit": "g", "item": "ground pork", "notes": "200g ground pork (slightly fatty, not lean)", "category": "meat"}, {"quantity": 100.0, "unit": "g", "item": "water chestnuts", "notes": "100g canned water chestnuts (or chopped spinach/cabbage)", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "sea salt", "notes": "1 teaspoon sea salt", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "sugar", "notes": "1 teaspoon fine sugar", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "teaspoon", "item": "ground pepper", "notes": "1/2 teaspoon ground black pepper", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "teaspoons", "item": "soy sauce", "notes": "2 teaspoons light soy sauce", "category": "condiments"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "teaspoons", "item": "sesame oil", "notes": "2 teaspoons sesame oil", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tablespoon", "item": "shaoxing huatiao wine", "notes": "1 tablespoon Shaoxing Huatiao wine", "category": "alcoholic beverages"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "scallions", "notes": "2 to 3 tablespoons of chopped scallions (spring onions)", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 25.0, "unit": "", "item": "dumpling wrappers", "notes": "25 to 30 store bought dumpling wrappers (the round kind, not the square wanton or spring roll wrappers)", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 24.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "flour to dust", "notes": "Plain flour to dust", "category": "baking"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "vegetable oil", "notes": "4 to 6 tablespoons vegetable oil (for 2 batches of cooking)", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 0.6666667, "unit": "cups", "item": "water", "notes": "2/3 cups water (for 2 batches of cooking)", "category": "beverages"}]'::jsonb, '["Place 200g of ground pork in a large mixing bowl. If preferred, pork may be substituted with ground chicken.", "Add 1 teaspoon of sea salt, 1 teaspoon of fine sugar, add 1/2 teaspoon of ground black pepper, 2 teaspoons of light soy sauce, 2 teaspoons of sesame oil and 1 tablespoon of Shaoxing Huatiao wine.", "Place 100g of canned water chestnuts in a chopper/blender. Chop the water chestnuts to small pieces.", "Add the chopped water chestnuts to the pork mixture. If preferred, use spinach or cabbage in place of water chestnuts.", "Add 2 to 3 tablespoons of finely chopped scallions or spring onions to the pork mixture.", "Combine all the filling ingredients well.", "Thaw the dumpling wrappers if they are frozen. Keep them well covered until they are ready to be used.", "Dust a dish generously with flour. This will hold the dumplings once they are made.", "Dust the table generously with flour. Carefully separate the sheets of dumpling wrappers and lay them on the table. Fill each wrapper with about 1.5 teaspoons of the prepared pork filling.", "Prepare a bowl of water. Dip finger into the water and lightly wet the rim of each dumpling wrapper.", "Bring the dumpling wrapper together till the opposite ends meet. Gently push the filling into the wrapper and pinch the top tip of the dumpling wrapper to seal it.", "From the centre of the dumpling, fold a pleat on ONE side and bring it to the other side of the dumpling. Fold towards the centre of the dumpling. Pinch to seal it.", "Repeat and create a 2nd pleat. Be mindful to pinch tight to seal the dumpling well. Repeat and create a 3rd pleat. Each side should have 3 pleats.", "Repeat the same pleating on the other end of the dumpling. Always ensure that the pleats face the centre of the dumpling.", "Place all prepared dumplings in a well floured dish ensuring that they do not touch each other. Set aside till ready to cook. They can also be frozen at this stage.", "To cook the potstickers, add 2 to 3 tablespoons of vegetable oil to a very hot frying pan. The potstickers should be cooked in at least 2 batches.", "When the oil is hot, add the dumplings ensuring that the flat surfaces face down. Pan fry till the bottoms of the dumplings are a nice golden brown.", "Add 1/3 cup of water to the pan. Cover the pan immediately and let the steam cook the dumplings for 4 to 5 minutes.", "Once the water has evaporated, remove the cover and let the dumplings sit in the hot pan for another minute for its base to crisp up again. These are now Chinese potstickers.", "Gently transfer the potstickers to a plate.", "Serve immediately.", "These Chinese potstickers are best served with a vinegar dip made with balsamic or black chinese vinegar and thinly sliced ginger. Soy sauce, chili oil or sesame oil may also be added to the dipping sauce."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/GNBC6TDX/chinese-potstickers', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/638693-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('five-spice-chinese-pork-stew', 'Five Spice Chinese Pork Stew', 6, 0, 0, '{"calories": 125, "protein": 7.19, "carbs": 14.63, "fat": 5.16, "saturated_fat": 0.84, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 3177.29, "potassium": null, "fiber": 2.39, "sugar": 6.62, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 4.3, "calcium": 58.24, "iron": 2.05}'::jsonb, ARRAY['chinese', 'asian', 'antipasti', 'soup', 'starter', 'snack', 'appetizer', 'antipasto', 'hor d''oeuvre', 'gluten free', 'dairy free', 'spoonacular'], '[{"quantity": 1.5, "unit": "kilo", "item": "pork paikut", "notes": "1 & 1/2 kilo pork paikut, sliced into cubes – you can use pork belly or spareribs as long as there is more meat than fat", "category": "meat"}, {"quantity": 6.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "water enough", "notes": "water enough to cover the pork by 1/2 inch more", "category": "beverages"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "tsp", "item": "five spice powder", "notes": "1/2 tsp Chinese five spice powder", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "cracked pepper", "notes": "1/2 tbsp cracked pepper", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "iodized salt", "notes": "1 tbsp iodized salt", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "", "item": "bay leaves", "notes": "3-5 bay leaves", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "", "item": "celery stalks", "notes": "2-4 celery stalks", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "vegetable oil", "notes": "2 tbsp vegetable oil", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "head", "item": "garlic", "notes": "1 head of garlic, minced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "medium", "item": "shallots/sibuyas na pula", "notes": "2 medium shallots/sibuyas na pula, sliced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "large", "item": "onion", "notes": "1 large white onion, sliced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "honey", "notes": "1 tbsp honey", "category": "nut butters, jams, and honey"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "apple cider vinegar", "notes": "2 tbsp apple cider vinegar", "category": "oil, vinegar, salad dressing"}, {"quantity": 0.75, "unit": "cup", "item": "soy sauce", "notes": "3/4 cup light soy sauce", "category": "condiments"}, {"quantity": 3.0, "unit": "cups", "item": "pork stock", "notes": "3 cups pork stock (the water used for boiling the pork)", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "", "item": "ginger", "notes": "1 ginger, two inches in length, sliced into 1/4 inch slices", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.5, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "anise seed", "notes": "1/2 tbsp anise seed", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "tbsp", "item": "cracked pepper", "notes": "1 /2 tbsp cracked pepper", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 198.0, "unit": "gram", "item": "mushrooms", "notes": "1 198gram can whole mushrooms, sliced in half (it''s chunkier that way)", "category": "canned and jarred"}]'::jsonb, '["In a large pot, add the pork with the rest of the ingredients for boiling.", "Add water, enough the cover by pork by 1/2 inch.", "Boil on medium heat until the pork is fork tender. Once done, remove the pork from the pot.", "Reserve the stock and run it through a fine sieve to strain the impurities.", "In a wok or large pan, heat the oil and add the garlic. Allow to toast but be careful not to burn it.", "Add the shallots and the white onion and saute until it sweats and goes slightly limp.", "Add the ginger and fry until very fragrant.", "Remove around 1/4 of the onion and ginger and reserve for garnish.", "Add the pork and mix everything well until the pork is lightly toasted, around 2-3 minutes.", "Add the pork stock, followed the the soy sauce.", "Add in the remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover the pot and allow the stew to reduce for 2  3 minutes.", "Add the mushrooms and cook for another minute.", "Remove from pan and serve hot, garnished with the sauteed onions and ginger, and with a heaping scoop of rice. Enjoy!"]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/LNTFHNH5/five-spice-chinese-pork-stew', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/643011-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
INSERT INTO public.recipes (slug, name, servings, prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes, nutrition, tags, ingredients, instructions, source_url, image_url, reheats_well, stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch) VALUES ('crab-wontons', 'Crab Wontons', 12, 0, 0, '{"calories": 46, "protein": 4.12, "carbs": 5.41, "fat": 0.81, "saturated_fat": 0.18, "polyunsaturated_fat": null, "monounsaturated_fat": null, "sodium": 194.23, "potassium": null, "fiber": 0, "sugar": 0.61, "vitamin_a": null, "vitamin_c": 0, "calcium": 47.08, "iron": 0.34}'::jsonb, ARRAY['chinese', 'asian', 'antipasti', 'starter', 'snack', 'appetizer', 'antipasto', 'hor d''oeuvre', 'pescatarian', 'spoonacular', 'baking'], '[{"quantity": 1.0, "unit": "can", "item": "crabmeat", "notes": "1 can 6 oz. white crabmeat, drained and chopped", "category": "canned and jarred"}, {"quantity": 4.0, "unit": "oz", "item": "cream cheese", "notes": "4 oz. fat free cream cheese, softened", "category": "cheese"}, {"quantity": 2.0, "unit": "tablespoons", "item": "reduced fat mayonnaise", "notes": "2 tablespoons reduced fat mayonnaise", "category": "condiments"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "tsp", "item": "soy sauce", "notes": "1/4 tsp. soy sauce", "category": "ethnic foods"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "tsp", "item": "garlic", "notes": "1/4 tsp. garlic, minced", "category": "produce"}, {"quantity": 0.25, "unit": "tsp", "item": "onion powder", "notes": "1/4 tsp. onion powder", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 12.0, "unit": "servings", "item": "ground pepper", "notes": "fresh ground pepper to taste", "category": "spices and seasonings"}, {"quantity": 12.0, "unit": "", "item": "won ton wrappers", "notes": "12 won ton wrappers", "category": "ethnic foods"}]'::jsonb, '["Preheat oven to 350F. Spray a mini muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray.", "In a medium bowl, combine crab meat, cream cheese, mayonaise, soy sauce, garlic, onion powder,and pepper.", "Mix until well combined.", "Place 1 won ton wrapper in each 12 mini muffin cups. The edges of the won ton wrappers will extend beyond the mini muffin tin cups and may need to be folded slightly. Fill the center of each won ton cup with crab mixture.", "Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until edges of cups are golden brown and filling is heated through."]'::jsonb, 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/ZM4M52TG/crab-wontons', 'https://img.spoonacular.com/recipes/640323-312x231.jpg', FALSE, 0, FALSE) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name, servings = EXCLUDED.servings, prep_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.prep_time_minutes, cook_time_minutes = EXCLUDED.cook_time_minutes, nutrition = EXCLUDED.nutrition, tags = EXCLUDED.tags, ingredients = EXCLUDED.ingredients, instructions = EXCLUDED.instructions, source_url = EXCLUDED.source_url, image_url = EXCLUDED.image_url, reheats_well = EXCLUDED.reheats_well, stores_days = EXCLUDED.stores_days, packs_well_as_lunch = EXCLUDED.packs_well_as_lunch;
